# ~/.config/git/allowed_signers — used by `git log --show-signature` and
# `git verify-commit` to confirm SSH-signed commits came from a key you
# trust. Without this file, signing works but local verification shows
# "no principal matched".
#
# Format: <email-or-pattern> <ssh-pubkey-line>
# Example:
#   346112+wernerglinka@users.noreply.github.com ssh-ed25519 AAAA...
#
# Populated by hand after the ed25519 key is generated, so this file may
# be empty on a fresh checkout. The email is hardcoded because the base
# ~/.gitconfig is identity-free by design and `git config --get
# user.email` only resolves inside the dev trees. To add the current
# machine's key:
#
#   printf '%s %s\n' \
#     "346112+wernerglinka@users.noreply.github.com" \
#     "$(cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub)" \
#     >> ~/.config/git/allowed_signers
346112+wernerglinka@users.noreply.github.com ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAICTf+wlq4SxMH6V2YU5Y4CQD9oWVYPfUFpeu3wZNforp 346112+wernerglinka@users.noreply.github.com
